00:02:55,738 --> 00:02:56,576
Again.

25
00:03:00,702 --> 00:03:01,615
Again.

26
00:03:05,878 --> 00:03:07,896
It took a long time...

27
00:03:08,864 --> 00:03:09,785
Two.

28
00:03:10,807 --> 00:03:11,720
Three.

29
00:03:12,784 --> 00:03:13,860
Four.

30
00:03:15,162 --> 00:03:16,021
Five.

31
00:03:18,252 --> 00:03:19,086
Six.

32
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:23,970
Number Seven?

33
00:03:25,650 --> 00:03:26,540
Again.

34
00:03:29,108 --> 00:03:30,243
Twelve.

35
00:03:34,304 --> 00:03:35,321
This is the first time...

36
00:03:35,606 --> 00:03:36,674
...you got all of them right.

37
00:03:40,122 --> 00:03:42,340
...until I can recognize
the faces of my loved ones.

38
00:04:15,522 --> 00:04:16,752
The hairstyle.

39
00:04:17,288 --> 00:04:18,160
The clothes.

40
00:04:18,325 --> 00:04:19,526
The gait.

41
00:04:19,752 --> 00:04:20,861
The scent.

42
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:21,841
Mother.

43
00:04:21,926 --> 00:04:22,927
The speech style.

44
00:04:23,134 --> 00:04:24,030
The habits.

45
00:04:25,533 --> 00:04:26,600
I'm back.

46
00:04:26,928 --> 00:04:29,569
Even when I used all those nuances...

47
00:04:29,892 --> 00:04:31,332
...to start recognizing my loved ones.

48
00:04:31,417 --> 00:04:32,436
I'm glad you're back.

49
00:04:33,429 --> 00:04:36,034
The one person
who I still couldn't recognize...

50
00:04:41,933 --> 00:04:43,350
...was myself.

51
00:04:53,272 --> 00:04:55,272
That's probably when it all started.

52
00:04:55,419 --> 00:04:56,806
My loved ones...

53
00:04:56,976 --> 00:04:58,565
...whom I can recognize...

54
00:04:58,996 --> 00:05:00,801
...and need to recognize.

55
00:05:01,749 --> 00:05:02,714
And I...

56
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:05,284
...was no longer part of them.

57
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:17,884
From that day on,
I have never loved myself.

58
00:05:18,710 --> 00:05:19,653
Ever.

59
00:05:20,854 --> 00:05:22,155
Can someone...

60
00:05:22,930 --> 00:05:23,924
...like me...

61
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:26,560
...love you...

62
00:05:28,286 --> 00:05:29,975
...and love myself?

63
00:05:30,906 --> 00:05:32,332
Will you be okay...

64
00:05:33,573 --> 00:05:34,432
...to be with me?

65
00:05:37,614 --> 00:05:38,872
Do you mean it?

66
00:05:39,890 --> 00:05:40,907
I do.

67
00:05:42,244 --> 00:05:43,510
I don't believe you.

68
00:05:46,782 --> 00:05:48,048
Prove it.

69
00:06:59,539 --> 00:07:00,829
Do you like me?

70
00:07:01,505 --> 00:07:02,353
Yes.

71
00:07:03,253 --> 00:07:05,044
Even when I'm not beautiful.

72
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:06,923
Even when you're not beautiful.

73
00:07:08,622 --> 00:07:09,591
Thank you...

74
00:07:12,326 --> 00:07:13,899
...for liking me.

75
00:07:17,878 --> 00:07:19,163
For still liking me...

76
00:07:21,183 --> 00:07:22,849
...even when I'm like this.

77
00:07:30,810 --> 00:07:32,410
What should we do about the contract?

78
00:07:36,505 --> 00:07:38,366
There's no such thing anymore.

79
00:07:39,567 --> 00:07:40,988
I already ripped it.

80
00:07:41,357 --> 00:07:42,276
The contract.

81
00:07:49,418 --> 00:07:52,123
Now, I'm the only one
who has the contracts.

82
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:54,837
That somehow makes me feel anxious.

83
00:08:02,197 --> 00:08:03,684
We broke up.

84
00:08:04,189 --> 00:08:05,532
But now we're dating.

85
00:08:06,504 --> 00:08:08,098
We have decided to date.

86
00:08:08,509 --> 00:08:09,510
But...

87
00:08:09,836 --> 00:08:11,836
...there will be articles
saying that we broke up.

88
00:08:16,344 --> 00:08:17,921
(Han Segye and Seo Dojae Broke Up)

89
00:08:19,822 --> 00:08:20,998
(Han Segye and Seo Dojae
Decided to Stay Friends)

90
00:08:30,445 --> 00:08:31,651
It just happened.

91
00:08:37,055 --> 00:08:39,571
Would you please do one thing at a time?

92
00:08:40,278 --> 00:08:41,398
One at a time!

93
00:08:43,579 --> 00:08:46,343
So you got yourself drunk
because of that jerk?

94
00:08:46,878 --> 00:08:48,703
Did you stop eating because of him?

95
00:08:48,803 --> 00:08:50,313
No. Never.

96
00:08:50,398 --> 00:08:54,886
That guy made you drink till you pass out
and starve yourself.

97
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,318
I will never let you date him.

98
00:08:57,707 --> 00:08:59,034
It's because of work stress.

99
00:08:59,119 --> 00:09:00,440
A hundred percent because of work.

100
00:09:00,648 --> 00:09:02,233
Yes. It's because of Chae Yoori.

101
00:09:02,324 --> 00:09:03,424
The next one...

102
00:09:04,161 --> 00:09:06,226
...is a bigger problem.

103
00:09:06,311 --> 00:09:08,182
You better answer me properly.

104
00:09:09,226 --> 00:09:10,229
Did you...

105
00:09:11,638 --> 00:09:13,189
...confess to him first?

106
00:09:14,384 --> 00:09:15,257
No.

107
00:09:16,244 --> 00:09:17,096
It was him.

108
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:18,159
I rejected him.

109
00:09:18,244 --> 00:09:19,614
I told him we need to end it.

110
00:09:19,789 --> 00:09:21,359
But he confessed to me.

111
00:09:21,515 --> 00:09:22,990
Then, that's fine.

112
00:09:23,607 --> 00:09:24,719
Woomi...

113
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:27,360
...I'm really sorry.

114
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:34,343
Reporter Park...

115
00:09:34,496 --> 00:09:36,597
...I have a great scoop for you.

116
00:09:41,598 --> 00:09:43,887
Wow. Unbelievable. They broke up.

117
00:09:43,972 --> 00:09:44,982
Already?

118
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:47,200
-I knew it.
-Because they're both busy?

119
00:09:47,285 --> 00:09:49,153
-Why would they date in the first place?
-What on earth?

120
00:09:49,238 --> 00:09:51,309
-Due to a difference in personality?
-How did they both meet?

121
00:09:51,394 --> 00:09:53,341
-They broke up to focus on work?
-It doesn't make sense.

122
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:55,896
-After all the fuss?
-It's obvious.

123
00:09:55,981 --> 00:09:57,981
(Han Segye and Seo Dojae Breakup?)

124
00:09:58,066 --> 00:09:59,206
Have you read the article?

125
00:09:59,291 --> 00:10:00,181
What article?

126
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:03,192
There's an article about Han Segye
and Mr. Seo breaking up.

127
00:10:03,277 --> 00:10:05,199
"Han Segye and Seo Dojae Broke Up"

128
00:10:05,284 --> 00:10:06,711
"...Decided to Stay Friends"

129
00:10:07,042 --> 00:10:09,208
"Han Segye's side confirms breakup"

130
00:10:10,831 --> 00:10:14,009
"Breakup reason was because
she wants to focus on her projects"

131
00:10:23,826 --> 00:10:25,471
I told you there will be news soon.

132
00:10:25,707 --> 00:10:27,581
When I heard of it from my source...

133
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,868
...I was so so shocked.

134
00:10:32,017 --> 00:10:33,286
This is why...

135
00:10:33,479 --> 00:10:35,618
...I can't really respect the family.

136
00:10:37,003 --> 00:10:38,467
Don't you agree, Ms. Kang?

137
00:10:39,866 --> 00:10:43,563
I'm sure you didn't call me
to act like friends and badmouth them.

138
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:46,518
I heard you called from Director Kim
and lectured him?

139
00:10:47,198 --> 00:10:49,858
Ms. Kang, I admire your tenacity.

140
00:10:49,943 --> 00:10:52,377
It's amazing. Bravo.

141
00:10:53,247 --> 00:10:54,541
But that Director Kim...

142
00:10:54,682 --> 00:10:58,172
...I really didn't expect
that he's such a bad guy.

143
00:11:00,421 --> 00:11:03,042
I also don't think you called me
to compliment me.

144
00:11:09,568 --> 00:11:11,066
Let's make a gamble.

145
00:11:11,669 --> 00:11:14,620
I have some talent for gambling, you know.

146
00:11:14,991 --> 00:11:16,011
I'm don't...

147
00:11:16,373 --> 00:11:18,021
...want to bet on Seo Dojae.

148
00:11:18,519 --> 00:11:20,582
I'm want to bet on Kang Sara.

149
00:11:20,782 --> 00:11:21,736
What do you think?

150
00:11:24,734 --> 00:11:26,058
In your dreams.

151
00:11:26,736 --> 00:11:29,417
You're supposed to play a game
with people of your own level.

152
00:11:29,502 --> 00:11:31,179
What? What did you say?

153
00:11:31,368 --> 00:11:34,604
I'm not going to fall
for your empty talks.

154
00:11:35,303 --> 00:11:36,508
On top of that...

155
00:11:36,945 --> 00:11:39,861
...I'm not really interested
in any of your plans.

156
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:47,456
Who does he think he is?
He doesn't even know his place.

157
00:11:47,659 --> 00:11:49,096
The chairman...

158
00:11:50,201 --> 00:11:51,856
...no matter how open-minded he is.

159
00:11:51,941 --> 00:11:53,872
...will he pass down the company
to his step-granddaughter...

160
00:11:53,957 --> 00:11:56,234
...instead of his own grandson?

161
00:11:57,411 --> 00:12:01,430
Are you asking that because
you think I don't know?

162
00:12:02,747 --> 00:12:04,552
Are you being like this
because you're trusting him?

163
00:12:06,242 --> 00:12:09,147
He's still living abroad, isn't he?

164
00:12:10,113 --> 00:12:12,788
Rumor has it he's having
the time of his life.

165
00:12:18,523 --> 00:12:20,668
You said he was crazy in love?

166
00:12:22,342 --> 00:12:24,766
Even crazy love... will come to an end.

167
00:12:24,851 --> 00:12:26,755
That's right. He's definitely crazy.
Plain crazy.

168
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:29,174
Didn't I told you to
keep a close eye on him?

169
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:31,104
So that he won't end up on the front page.

170
00:12:31,195 --> 00:12:33,917
I will do my best so that it won't happen.

171
00:12:34,001 --> 00:12:36,254
You're sure good with your words.

172
00:12:36,381 --> 00:12:37,712
Easier said than done.

173
00:12:37,903 --> 00:12:38,918
Get on it.

174
00:12:39,003 --> 00:12:40,844
If not, I'll deduct your pay.

175
00:12:41,312 --> 00:12:42,329
Excuse me?

176
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:48,453
"Deduct my pay"?

177
00:12:50,738 --> 00:12:52,021
Hello. How are you?

178
00:12:53,197 --> 00:12:54,927
I am not fine.

179
00:12:55,012 --> 00:12:57,376
Who said you can release that statement?

180
00:12:57,478 --> 00:12:59,136
You told them Mr. Seo got dumped?

181
00:12:59,303 --> 00:13:00,577
Does it even make sense?

182
00:13:00,662 --> 00:13:01,842
Why not?

183
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,301
That's what Segye said.

184
00:13:04,557 --> 00:13:06,246
She said she dumped him.

185
00:13:07,334 --> 00:13:09,334
It's not true anyway.

186
00:13:09,802 --> 00:13:12,325
We already took this much of a risk.

187
00:13:12,953 --> 00:13:14,953
What more do you expect?

188
00:13:16,807 --> 00:13:19,114
Seems like you don't understand
what it means to take a risk.

189
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:20,848
Yes, I don't know.

190
00:13:22,156 --> 00:13:23,675
Is that an office jargon?

191
00:13:23,942 --> 00:13:25,189
You see...

192
00:13:25,450 --> 00:13:27,779
...I'm used to working hands-on jobs.

193
00:13:28,505 --> 00:13:30,633
Do you think it'll only badly affect us?

194
00:13:30,718 --> 00:13:32,838
Your side will suffer too.

195
00:13:32,923 --> 00:13:34,244
Exactly...

196
00:13:34,613 --> 00:13:38,437
If we're both going to be affected,
our side wants the less damage.

197
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,953
Geez.

198
00:13:41,329 --> 00:13:43,894
It's impossible to talk
with someone on your level.

199
00:13:44,063 --> 00:13:45,987
Do you finally see it now?

200
00:13:46,216 --> 00:13:48,385
How low your level is.

201
00:13:50,210 --> 00:13:52,459
If you've realized that,

202
00:13:52,543 --> 00:13:54,543
please stop bothering me.

203
00:13:54,648 --> 00:13:57,777
Go complain to your boss first.

204
00:14:02,347 --> 00:14:03,700
Thanks for the meal.

205
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:16,002
I can't live in peace
because of my own son.

206
00:14:18,398 --> 00:14:19,597
Stop. Stop.

207
00:14:19,727 --> 00:14:22,549
Honey, that's not weed.
That's a flowering plant.

208
00:14:22,634 --> 00:14:24,643
We need to weed them out
if they act like one.

209
00:14:24,727 --> 00:14:26,467
No. Don't be like that.

210
00:14:27,555 --> 00:14:30,094
When a plant is suffering,

211
00:14:30,267 --> 00:14:33,102
you have to pat it down with fine soil.

212
00:14:33,306 --> 00:14:35,192
Can you please meet Dojae?

213
00:14:35,276 --> 00:14:37,207
He won't listen to me.

214
00:14:37,788 --> 00:14:40,889
No one listens to you as well as he does.

215
00:14:41,693 --> 00:14:44,434
I think I'm going to blow up if I see him.

216
00:14:45,186 --> 00:14:48,117
So can you go and slow talk to him for me?

217
00:14:55,696 --> 00:14:58,166
How are you feeling?

218
00:14:58,867 --> 00:15:01,383
I'm sorry for ruining the trip.

219
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:03,207
Why would you apologize to me
for getting sick?

220
00:15:03,958 --> 00:15:06,676
You should apologize to yourself
for not treating yourself well.

221
00:15:09,207 --> 00:15:10,247
I'm sorry.

222
00:15:12,176 --> 00:15:14,176
Do you have a gun training today?

223
00:15:15,786 --> 00:15:16,736
Will you be okay?

224
00:15:16,821 --> 00:15:17,698
Yes.

225
00:15:18,028 --> 00:15:20,082
I'm meeting the action team today.

226
00:15:20,487 --> 00:15:21,349
Good.

227
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:23,730
We're going to start shooting soon.

228
00:15:24,219 --> 00:15:25,439
Take care of yourself until then.

229
00:15:25,689 --> 00:15:26,526
You may leave.

230
00:15:28,354 --> 00:15:29,338
Director Lee...

231
00:15:30,269 --> 00:15:32,297
...can I ask you something?

232
00:15:32,602 --> 00:15:33,459
Sure.

233
00:15:35,737 --> 00:15:37,237
Why did you pick her?

234
00:15:37,807 --> 00:15:38,704
Yoori?

235
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:39,774
Yes.

236
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,905
What do you like about her?

237
00:15:48,327 --> 00:15:49,286
It's because...

238
00:15:50,286 --> 00:15:51,600
...she's different from you.

239
00:15:52,161 --> 00:15:53,376
What is the difference?

240
00:15:54,656 --> 00:15:55,789
I want to know.

241
00:15:56,682 --> 00:15:57,783
Yoori...

242
00:15:58,429 --> 00:16:01,345
Her problem is that
she loves herself too much.

243
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:03,317
Unlike you.

244
00:16:03,603 --> 00:16:04,779
You two...

245
00:16:05,977 --> 00:16:07,662
...have very different problems.

246
00:16:08,396 --> 00:16:09,547
So...

247
00:16:11,535 --> 00:16:13,275
...please get along with her, Segye.

248
00:16:20,017 --> 00:16:21,256
Hold here.

249
00:16:30,686 --> 00:16:32,673
Segye, I heard you broke up?

250
00:16:32,757 --> 00:16:35,112
You better not act up
when I'm holding a gun.

251
00:16:35,196 --> 00:16:37,403
Rumor has it that you two broke up
because of the tabloid.

252
00:16:37,488 --> 00:16:38,557
Is that right?

253
00:16:40,084 --> 00:16:42,273
This is awkward. Why are you
suddenly being so polite?

254
00:16:42,358 --> 00:16:43,804
You weren't like this a few days ago.

255
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:48,578
Me?

256
00:16:48,982 --> 00:16:49,937
When?

257
00:16:52,247 --> 00:16:53,947
"Me"?

258
00:16:54,865 --> 00:16:56,532
-"When"?
-Oh my.

259
00:16:56,685 --> 00:16:58,472
I must have been drunk

260
00:16:58,609 --> 00:17:00,514
I have a bad drunk habit.

261
00:17:01,038 --> 00:17:03,108
I blackout too sometimes.

262
00:17:03,725 --> 00:17:05,643
But when did you break up?

263
00:17:05,727 --> 00:17:07,742
Is that why you acted
like that during the trip?

264
00:17:07,826 --> 00:17:10,442
Did you get yourself drunk
to nurse your broken heart?

265
00:17:10,526 --> 00:17:11,967
You said you didn't remember anything.

266
00:17:12,798 --> 00:17:14,227
Yes. I don't.

267
00:17:16,437 --> 00:17:18,036
-Segye, by the way...
-Hey.

268
00:17:18,776 --> 00:17:20,007
Don't talk to me.

269
00:17:21,606 --> 00:17:22,762
You know what?

270
00:17:22,846 --> 00:17:25,135
I'm the one who saved your life.

271
00:17:25,225 --> 00:17:28,418
If I hadn't gone and asked for help,
you wouldn't be standing here now.

272
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:31,086
Gosh, she's so noisy.

273
00:17:31,349 --> 00:17:32,935
Should I shoot?

274
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:33,987
Excuse me?

275
00:17:35,056 --> 00:17:36,657
But it'll be a waste of bullets, right?

276
00:17:39,056 --> 00:17:40,526
That's not true.

277
00:17:40,827 --> 00:17:42,897
Please write the article
based on the truth.

278
00:17:44,203 --> 00:17:47,238
We had an amicable breakup
for our own good.

279
00:17:47,957 --> 00:17:49,019
That's all.

280
00:17:52,592 --> 00:17:55,210
I can't live because I'm so humiliated.

281
00:17:56,368 --> 00:17:58,528
Do you know what I just
went through today?

282
00:17:59,149 --> 00:18:01,013
When did you two even start dating?

283
00:18:02,141 --> 00:18:03,033
Yesterday?

284
00:18:03,124 --> 00:18:04,902
Then what's with the news?

285
00:18:05,356 --> 00:18:06,289
Well...

286
00:18:06,741 --> 00:18:07,817
...It just happened.

287
00:18:10,626 --> 00:18:12,113
-I want to quit.
-You can't.

288
00:18:12,197 --> 00:18:13,712
Then, I want a pay raise.

289
00:18:13,796 --> 00:18:14,856
I can't.

290
00:18:15,093 --> 00:18:16,227
Then, I'm going home.

291
00:18:16,312 --> 00:18:17,201
You can't.

292
00:18:18,636 --> 00:18:20,284
There are 30 minutes left.

293
00:18:26,386 --> 00:18:28,043
-Hello.
-Mr. Seo...

294
00:18:28,128 --> 00:18:30,601
...did you make an appointment
with your father?

295
00:18:32,041 --> 00:18:32,974
Father.

296
00:18:33,401 --> 00:18:34,261
What brings you here?

297
00:18:34,346 --> 00:18:37,687
Well... I was just passing by.

298
00:18:38,987 --> 00:18:41,286
I sort of miss my son, so...

299
00:18:41,642 --> 00:18:44,958
Is that what my mom told you to say?

300
00:18:48,227 --> 00:18:49,907
A rubber tree...

301
00:18:50,715 --> 00:18:52,367
...is a tree that must get hurt...

302
00:18:52,574 --> 00:18:54,967
...to become useful.

303
00:18:55,113 --> 00:18:56,479
You know "slash and burn", right?

304
00:18:56,564 --> 00:18:58,103
They burn all the plants...

305
00:18:58,188 --> 00:19:00,914
...to grow a new life from the ground.

306
00:19:06,288 --> 00:19:08,229
There is no tree that doesn't have a knot.

307
00:19:08,510 --> 00:19:10,550
Even though you failed at love...

308
00:19:10,925 --> 00:19:13,386
-...you can use that...
-It's not what you think.

309
00:19:14,616 --> 00:19:17,487
Sure. It's fine.
Everyone is like that at first.

310
00:19:17,586 --> 00:19:19,463
That how you'll grow up...

311
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:21,150
...and learn to forget about it.

312
00:19:21,235 --> 00:19:22,692
I told you, it's not like that.

313
00:19:26,009 --> 00:19:28,009
Don't be so bitter about it.

314
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:29,791
If it's too hard for you,

315
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:32,407
it's okay to cry.

316
00:19:32,507 --> 00:19:33,490
I'm not having a hard time.

317
00:19:33,575 --> 00:19:35,597
You'll meet someone better.

318
00:19:35,907 --> 00:19:38,756
She doesn't know how to appreciate you.

319
00:19:38,917 --> 00:19:41,417
I mean, you're such a great guy...

320
00:19:44,886 --> 00:19:46,017
Is there...

321
00:19:46,556 --> 00:19:49,457
...any chance that she'll
give you a second chance?

322
00:19:53,526 --> 00:19:56,406
I see. I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have said that.

323
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:01,742
Do you want to go for a drink?

324
00:20:15,832 --> 00:20:16,924
This won't do.

325
00:20:17,009 --> 00:20:18,261
We need to do something.

326
00:20:18,464 --> 00:20:19,968
I totally agree.

327
00:20:21,028 --> 00:20:24,579
I mean, why did you release the article?
You only made things worse.

328
00:20:24,694 --> 00:20:27,065
You're the one who wanted
to terminate the contract.

329
00:20:27,361 --> 00:20:30,163
So you just agree to it when I said that?

330
00:20:30,248 --> 00:20:31,777
Shouldn't have I?

331
00:20:32,136 --> 00:20:34,204
You're so senseless.

332
00:20:35,866 --> 00:20:37,534
I'm still not used
to those kinds of things.

333
00:20:37,619 --> 00:20:38,722
Don't say that!

334
00:20:38,806 --> 00:20:39,907
Why?

335
00:20:40,434 --> 00:20:41,463
You don't like...

336
00:20:42,154 --> 00:20:43,158
...this version of me?

337
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:45,447
No. It just makes me pity you.

338
00:20:47,876 --> 00:20:49,846
It breaks my heart
when I feel sorry for you.

339
00:20:50,993 --> 00:20:51,948
I'm touched.

340
00:20:52,657 --> 00:20:55,758
Geez. Why would you be touched,
when it's something so obvious.

341
00:20:57,556 --> 00:21:00,411
By the way, do you notice
any difference today?

342
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:03,413
That's the question
that men hate the most.

343
00:21:03,497 --> 00:21:04,406
I know.

344
00:21:06,774 --> 00:21:07,634
The earrings.

345
00:21:07,796 --> 00:21:08,780
They look good on you.

346
00:21:09,407 --> 00:21:12,396
I knew it. You're definitely
different from other men.

347
00:21:13,078 --> 00:21:15,075
It's you who have great taste in men.

348
00:21:17,507 --> 00:21:19,776
Are you complimenting me or yourself?

349
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:22,913
Me?

350
00:21:22,998 --> 00:21:24,381
Wait a second. Stay still.

351
00:21:29,586 --> 00:21:30,474
Done.

352
00:21:31,286 --> 00:21:32,242
What did you do?

353
00:21:32,327 --> 00:21:33,640
I didn't do anything.

354
00:21:33,957 --> 00:21:35,496
Oh no. I should head home now.

355
00:21:36,642 --> 00:21:38,058
See you at our next secret date.

356
00:21:40,737 --> 00:21:41,796
Han Segye.

357
00:21:43,066 --> 00:21:44,352
Call me when you get home.

358
00:21:44,437 --> 00:21:45,305
Why?

359
00:21:45,430 --> 00:21:46,570
Otherwise, I'll be worried.

360
00:22:01,436 --> 00:22:04,550
Oh my goodness. What's gotten into him?
He's acting like a real boyfriend.

361
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:10,429
(I just got home)

362
00:22:14,437 --> 00:22:15,680
Where have you been?

363
00:22:15,765 --> 00:22:17,083
Geez. You surprised me.

364
00:22:18,995 --> 00:22:19,996
Well...

365
00:22:20,373 --> 00:22:23,413
...my friend's father suddenly
passed away. So I went to visit.

366
00:22:25,794 --> 00:22:27,964
Your friend's father passed away...?

367
00:22:28,616 --> 00:22:31,815
So you went to the funeral
wearing those pretty earrings?

368
00:22:36,687 --> 00:22:38,534
Did you went to see "Uncle"?

369
00:22:38,619 --> 00:22:39,841
At a time like this?

370
00:22:40,589 --> 00:22:41,882
How did you know?

371
00:22:42,049 --> 00:22:43,163
That his nickname is "Uncle"?

372
00:22:43,248 --> 00:22:45,378
Why don't you take a guess?

373
00:22:45,897 --> 00:22:49,306
It's because you rambled
about it in the interview.

374
00:22:50,806 --> 00:22:51,643
I see.

375
00:22:51,728 --> 00:22:52,822
"I see"?

376
00:22:54,083 --> 00:22:55,620
That's all you can say,

377
00:22:55,705 --> 00:22:57,927
while I'm in the midst of
canceling all of your interviews?

378
00:23:01,312 --> 00:23:04,993
Go ask you Uncle to smoothly cancel...

379
00:23:05,356 --> 00:23:08,157
...your T'road Airline interview.

380
00:23:08,487 --> 00:23:10,071
Sure. Should I do that?

381
00:23:16,927 --> 00:23:18,026
No.

382
00:23:19,336 --> 00:23:20,266
Let's not cancel it.

383
00:23:20,351 --> 00:23:22,757
Why? What are you planning to do?

384
00:23:22,938 --> 00:23:24,267
I'm going to turn a crisis...

385
00:23:24,729 --> 00:23:25,692
...into an opportunity.

386
00:23:32,816 --> 00:23:35,433
I'm not sure if this
is a really good idea.

387
00:23:35,517 --> 00:23:36,760
Trust me.

388
00:23:41,056 --> 00:23:42,126
This is unbelievable.

389
00:23:42,386 --> 00:23:44,657
-This is unexpected.
-Why is she here?

390
00:23:45,397 --> 00:23:46,497
She's here.

391
00:23:53,096 --> 00:23:54,813
OMG. I have big news.

392
00:23:54,897 --> 00:23:57,339
(What is it? What happened?)

393
00:24:06,346 --> 00:24:07,292
This is huge!

394
00:24:07,376 --> 00:24:08,546
Why?

395
00:24:08,631 --> 00:24:10,062
Why? What happened?

396
00:24:10,147 --> 00:24:12,081
What is it? What happened?

397
00:24:12,166 --> 00:24:13,173
What's going on?

398
00:24:13,257 --> 00:24:14,921
What is it? Tell me.

399
00:24:16,331 --> 00:24:17,609
Han Segye is in the lobby right now.

400
00:24:20,388 --> 00:24:21,240
OMG!

401
00:24:21,536 --> 00:24:23,011
-That's huge.
-Han Segye?

402
00:24:46,757 --> 00:24:48,853
Han Segye is going up to our floor.

403
00:24:49,757 --> 00:24:51,086
What should we do?

404
00:24:52,266 --> 00:24:53,158
Oh my...

405
00:24:54,197 --> 00:24:57,497
Hey, hey, hey. What's going on?

406
00:24:57,596 --> 00:24:58,791
Why is she here?
I thought they broke up.

407
00:24:58,876 --> 00:25:00,653
-Is she here to meet Mr. Seo.
-Mr. Seo?

408
00:25:00,737 --> 00:25:03,450
-Should I go out and find out?
-Hey, it'll be so obvious if you do.

409
00:25:05,907 --> 00:25:09,691
I have no idea how I should
handle this right now.

410
00:25:09,776 --> 00:25:13,611
Mr. Seo. This is the model of the aircraft
that we are planning to buy.

411
00:25:15,639 --> 00:25:17,563
You need to approve this
so that we can proceed.

412
00:25:17,647 --> 00:25:20,227
I'm here.
I'm heading to the interview location.

413
00:25:25,081 --> 00:25:27,226
-Where are you going?
-Give that to me.

414
00:25:27,423 --> 00:25:28,583
You want me to deduct your salary?

415
00:25:29,727 --> 00:25:31,497
Big news! Big news!

416
00:25:31,897 --> 00:25:33,697
What is it? Why?

417
00:25:35,167 --> 00:25:37,087
There. Arrived.

418
00:25:37,366 --> 00:25:39,060
Han Segye. Lobby.

419
00:25:39,145 --> 00:25:41,383
Han Segye just arrived and
is walking through the lobby.

420
00:25:41,507 --> 00:25:43,606
What is she really goes
into Mr. Seo's office?

421
00:25:43,707 --> 00:25:46,417
-What should we do?
-I will go and take a look.

422
00:25:46,517 --> 00:25:48,192
I'll act like I'm lost.

423
00:25:48,276 --> 00:25:50,462
Wait. Why would someone get lost
at his own workplace?

424
00:25:50,546 --> 00:25:52,715
-You're a team leader, on top of that.
-You're right.

425
00:25:53,278 --> 00:25:54,907
Take this toothbrush.
Go brush your teeth.

426
00:25:55,011 --> 00:25:56,785
It's way past lunchtime.
Why would I brush my teeth now?

427
00:25:56,870 --> 00:25:57,995
That'll be more suspicious.

428
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,556
Pretend like you have braces on.

429
00:25:59,657 --> 00:26:01,098
You have to brush often
if you have braces.

430
00:26:01,183 --> 00:26:02,322
I don't have braces.

431
00:26:03,190 --> 00:26:05,776
Say you have lingual braces.
They're attached to the inner sides.

432
00:26:05,861 --> 00:26:06,931
Wow. She's a genius.

433
00:26:51,348 --> 00:26:52,668
I guess you come to work.

434
00:26:53,076 --> 00:26:54,171
I guess you're going to work.

435
00:26:54,256 --> 00:26:55,607
I hope the interview goes well...

436
00:26:55,970 --> 00:26:57,253
...as the Chief of Strategic Planning.

437
00:27:03,526 --> 00:27:04,705
Of course it will.

438
00:27:05,141 --> 00:27:06,648
I'm the model of the company, after all.

439
00:27:08,096 --> 00:27:09,167
They shook hands.

440
00:27:11,767 --> 00:27:12,727
Have a good day.

441
00:27:17,077 --> 00:27:17,964
Oh...

442
00:27:20,072 --> 00:27:21,310
Call me when you're done.

443
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:22,977
Let's have a meal together.

444
00:27:23,070 --> 00:27:23,982
Sure.

445
00:27:24,447 --> 00:27:25,424
It'll be my treat.

446
00:27:25,517 --> 00:27:26,355
Sure.

447
00:27:33,056 --> 00:27:35,157
Wow. Awesome. Did you just see that?

448
00:27:35,257 --> 00:27:36,868
For a moment,
I thought we're in Hollywood.

449
00:27:36,953 --> 00:27:37,886
They're so cool.

450
00:27:38,026 --> 00:27:39,619
They're the one who just broke up,

451
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:41,450
but why do I feel like
I'm the one who was dumped.

452
00:27:41,888 --> 00:27:42,731
What?

453
00:27:43,888 --> 00:27:46,127
Oh my gosh. That was the first time
we talked casually.

454
00:27:46,212 --> 00:27:47,012
I know.

455
00:27:47,096 --> 00:27:49,350
Wow. Your acting skills
have improved a bit.

456
00:27:49,435 --> 00:27:51,806
I was very nervous.
Looks like it wasn't obvious.

457
00:27:51,907 --> 00:27:54,066
No wonder your hand was cold.

458
00:27:56,207 --> 00:27:59,311
I'm sorry. A fellow actress texted me.

459
00:27:59,447 --> 00:28:00,492
Shall we continue?

460
00:28:00,576 --> 00:28:02,863
It looks like you two
are still in good terms.

461
00:28:02,947 --> 00:28:05,902
Actually, we were worried
that you'd cancel the interview.

462
00:28:07,187 --> 00:28:11,266
I don't see the need to avoid each other
just because we broke up.

463
00:28:11,427 --> 00:28:13,011
I consider him a good friend.

464
00:28:13,096 --> 00:28:15,561
I also respect him as a person a lot.

465
00:28:16,366 --> 00:28:18,710
-Can we start the shoot now?
-Sure.

466
00:28:24,806 --> 00:28:28,263
Is that what you call
"a cold but handsome man"?

467
00:28:35,816 --> 00:28:37,286
Yes. Hold on a second.

468
00:28:37,653 --> 00:28:39,143
This is related to business.

469
00:28:39,917 --> 00:28:43,717
I've never texted you regarding business.
Who are you actually texting to?

470
00:28:43,886 --> 00:28:46,752
Yes. Just a minute. I won't take long.

471
00:28:47,056 --> 00:28:48,899
Are you even listening to me?

472
00:28:50,767 --> 00:28:52,919
-Sir!
-What? What did you say?

473
00:28:54,737 --> 00:28:56,014
It's nothing.

474
00:28:57,036 --> 00:28:58,899
What should I do know?

475
00:28:59,036 --> 00:29:00,237
You can...

476
00:29:02,106 --> 00:29:03,177
...go home.

477
00:29:04,876 --> 00:29:05,947
Go home?

478
00:29:06,668 --> 00:29:08,346
-Already?
-Yes.

479
00:29:08,529 --> 00:29:09,432
Go home.

480
00:29:17,700 --> 00:29:18,711
Hey.

481
00:29:19,037 --> 00:29:19,884
Hand me your phone.

482
00:29:20,457 --> 00:29:22,714
-Why?
-It's worrying me to death.

483
00:29:22,799 --> 00:29:24,170
Give me your phone. I'm confiscating it.

484
00:29:24,497 --> 00:29:26,869
Why? I did a good job today, didn't I?

485
00:29:27,397 --> 00:29:30,322
You're just dying to
show off, weren't you?

486
00:29:30,437 --> 00:29:32,922
What are you talking about?

487
00:29:33,106 --> 00:29:35,346
Then, what's with the profile picture
on your messenger?

488
00:29:35,447 --> 00:29:36,803
-What?
-You know what I mean.

489
00:29:36,888 --> 00:29:39,702
The hand. That's Seo Dojae's hand.

490
00:29:47,187 --> 00:29:49,995
What do you mean?
This is just a stock photo.

491
00:29:50,727 --> 00:29:51,922
Are you a kid?

492
00:29:52,427 --> 00:29:53,497
Never mind.

493
00:29:53,757 --> 00:29:55,665
This also an insult to kids.

494
00:29:55,767 --> 00:29:58,820
Even kids these days
don't date like you do.

495
00:30:22,163 --> 00:30:24,256
Why are you suddenly putting on perfume?

496
00:30:24,586 --> 00:30:25,825
What's wrong?

497
00:30:26,356 --> 00:30:28,041
It's for you!

498
00:30:28,136 --> 00:30:30,749
I want to lift the mood up,
the ambiance and the conversation.

499
00:30:31,850 --> 00:30:34,190
Geez. The smell is too strong. Seriously.

500
00:30:35,437 --> 00:30:36,383
Look forward.

501
00:30:37,237 --> 00:30:40,064
Hey. We might get in an accident.
Look forward.

502
00:30:41,876 --> 00:30:44,606
I'm not going anywhere.

503
00:30:44,707 --> 00:30:46,761
I'll leave after I see you go inside.

504
00:30:46,846 --> 00:30:47,933
I'm being serious.

505
00:30:48,017 --> 00:30:49,903
I'm going to watch you go inside...

506
00:30:49,987 --> 00:30:53,038
...and wait outside for 30 minutes...

507
00:30:53,123 --> 00:30:54,686
...before I leave.

508
00:30:55,643 --> 00:30:56,902
I'm going inside now.

509
00:30:56,987 --> 00:30:58,532
Watch me. I'm going inside.

510
00:31:05,272 --> 00:31:06,290
You should...

511
00:31:06,762 --> 00:31:08,019
...be careful no matter what.

512
00:31:08,167 --> 00:31:10,267
Stay put.

513
00:31:10,815 --> 00:31:13,582
And don't even think
about causing trouble.

514
00:31:13,937 --> 00:31:15,054
Got it.

515
00:31:42,267 --> 00:31:43,630
Gosh, that girl.

516
00:31:51,009 --> 00:31:53,447
What kind of a password is "10041004"?

517
00:31:53,546 --> 00:31:55,009
Is that supposed to mean "angel"?

518
00:31:55,094 --> 00:31:57,105
What? Do you want me
to change it to something unrelated?

519
00:31:57,190 --> 00:31:58,064
Like "0116"?

520
00:31:58,149 --> 00:31:59,731
But that's also related now.

521
00:32:02,487 --> 00:32:06,002
I told you not to say things
as if it's not a big deal.

522
00:32:08,356 --> 00:32:09,826
I like how your perfume smells.

523
00:32:12,296 --> 00:32:13,230
Don't you need to do this?

524
00:32:13,486 --> 00:32:15,123
I no longer have to do that to know...

525
00:32:15,207 --> 00:32:16,707
...that it's your scent.

526
00:32:19,214 --> 00:32:21,069
I should only wear
this perfume from now on.

527
00:32:21,276 --> 00:32:22,960
I can't change my perfume as I please.

528
00:32:23,227 --> 00:32:25,027
Being in a relationship
can be so complicated.

529
00:32:25,753 --> 00:32:27,508
Don't think that it's complicated.

530
00:32:27,593 --> 00:32:30,833
I'd appreciate it if you think of it
as being consistent.

531
00:32:31,086 --> 00:32:33,114
I'd also appreciate it if you do the same.

532
00:32:34,287 --> 00:32:37,351
By the way, it's so thrilling
to be in a secret relationship.

533
00:32:37,974 --> 00:32:39,702
I have no idea that having
secrets can be so fun.

534
00:32:40,470 --> 00:32:42,690
It used to make me feel
anxious, sad and lonely.

535
00:32:43,490 --> 00:32:45,830
Now, we can be anxious, sad...

536
00:32:46,336 --> 00:32:47,635
...and lonely together.

537
00:32:49,036 --> 00:32:53,207
Shouldn't we aim to not be
anxious, sad and lonely together?

538
00:32:53,369 --> 00:32:56,103
I should try my best not to then.

539
00:32:56,731 --> 00:32:57,857
That's better.

