688
00:42:59,952 --> 00:43:01,219
I could never do that!

689
00:43:01,549 --> 00:43:02,981
What's the point of just burying them?

690
00:43:03,066 --> 00:43:04,644
The body will just decay anyway.

691
00:43:04,729 --> 00:43:09,463
I think I'd feel better if I knew
my child's heart is beating somewhere.

692
00:43:21,477 --> 00:43:25,697
Have you decided
which call to respond to, Juliano?

693
00:43:31,468 --> 00:43:34,520
I've made my mind a long time ago,

694
00:43:34,972 --> 00:43:35,961
Father.

695
00:44:06,547 --> 00:44:08,267
Just come home.

696
00:44:09,587 --> 00:44:11,028
How did you know to find me here?

697
00:44:11,299 --> 00:44:12,796
It doesn't matter.

698
00:44:12,979 --> 00:44:14,521
Just come back home...

699
00:44:15,240 --> 00:44:18,325
...before your mother passes away.

700
00:44:18,607 --> 00:44:19,508
Dad.

701
00:44:20,186 --> 00:44:22,078
I can't live the way she wants.

702
00:44:22,655 --> 00:44:24,634
I get it, so come back.

703
00:44:28,279 --> 00:44:29,399
I mean...

704
00:44:29,739 --> 00:44:32,666
