00:50:34,989 --> 00:50:36,075
This is...

807
00:50:36,301 --> 00:50:39,365
I heard you're trying to
find my weakness.

808
00:50:39,977 --> 00:50:40,884
But...

809
00:50:41,499 --> 00:50:43,828
...it seems I've found
your weakness instead.

810
00:50:44,661 --> 00:50:45,559
Just now.

811
00:50:48,441 --> 00:50:50,009
I don't understand
what you're talking about.

812
00:50:52,808 --> 00:50:54,306
I'm not her weakness.

813
00:50:55,529 --> 00:50:57,288
I'll be moving out of this house soon.

814
00:51:05,999 --> 00:51:07,819
Thank you for everything.

815
00:51:08,838 --> 00:51:10,083
Hey, Ryu Eunho.

816
00:51:11,647 --> 00:51:12,950
You guys should get going too.

817
00:51:14,155 --> 00:51:15,377
We'll talk tomorrow.

818
00:51:25,949 --> 00:51:27,025
I told you.

819
00:51:27,834 --> 00:51:29,895
I told you we're the bad guys.

820
00:51:37,059 --> 00:51:40,150
This is the rest of the chandelier's price
after deducting the pay for my work.

821
00:51:41,216 --> 00:51:42,759
Do you even know how much it was?

822
00:51:42,844 --> 00:51:44,026
I looked it up.

823
00:51:44,237 --> 00:51:45,681
The cheapest one costs 388,000 won.

824
00:51:46,347 --> 00:51:48,115
You're more thrifty than I thought.

825
00:51:49,158 --> 00:51:50,324
Also, this one...

826
00:51:50,962 --> 00:51:53,227
...is my small token of appreciation...

827
00:51:53,823 --> 00:51:55,837
...for letting me live and eat here.

828
00:52:04,843 --> 00:52:06,661
What are you telling your friends?

829
00:52:06,746 --> 00:52:08,305
I'll tell them the truth.

830
00:52:10,040 --> 00:52:11,087
The truth?

831
00:52:11,172 --> 00:52:12,822
That I was working here.

832
00:52:16,831 --> 00:52:17,939
When are you moving out?

833
00:52:18,382 --> 00:52:19,289
Tomorrow.

834
00:52:20,726 --> 00:52:22,145
When did you decide that?

835
00:52:22,229 --> 00:52:23,068
Today.

836
00:52:30,948 --> 00:52:32,116
Will you come back...

837
00:52:32,841 --> 00:52:33,988
...if I call you?

838
00:52:37,601 --> 00:52:38,905
I didn't mean anything else.

839
00:52:40,471 --> 00:52:42,965
I'm just asking because
I can't be bothered to hire someone new.

840
00:52:43,234 --> 00:52:45,227
Even if I hired someone...

841
00:52:45,338 --> 00:52:48,191
...it'll take a while until they adjust.

842
00:52:49,273 --> 00:52:50,468
Are you going to call me?

843
00:52:53,394 --> 00:52:54,566
Then, I'll come back.

844
00:53:01,188 --> 00:53:03,985
When did you find out about
the cost of the chandelier?

845
00:53:05,709 --> 00:53:06,953
From the beginning.

846
00:53:11,949 --> 00:53:13,888
Seriously, the kids these days...

847
00:53:14,302 --> 00:53:16,219
...can be so reckless.

848
00:53:20,289 --> 00:53:21,330
Fine then.

849
00:53:22,541 --> 00:53:23,488
I'll call you.

850
00:53:24,377 --> 00:53:25,331
Come back then.

851
00:54:18,940 --> 00:54:20,271
It's too sweet.

852
00:54:54,309 --> 00:54:56,128
I told him I don't eat breakfast.

853
00:55:42,186 --> 00:55:43,792
How nice.

854
00:55:43,877 --> 00:55:45,402
I feel better already.

855
00:55:47,404 --> 00:55:49,451
Hangover is indeed best treated...

856
00:55:49,769 --> 00:55:51,384
...with rice noodles.

857
00:55:56,213 --> 00:55:57,120
About last night...

858
00:55:57,205 --> 00:55:58,792
-Let's just eat.
-Okay.

859
00:56:02,582 --> 00:56:03,958
You're the one who befriended the enemy.

860
00:56:04,043 --> 00:56:05,571
Why should we be sorry...

861
00:56:06,333 --> 00:56:07,597
Get your facts straight.

862
00:56:07,682 --> 00:56:10,409
I've had many chances,
but I didn't tell her anything about you.

863
00:56:13,557 --> 00:56:14,927
Are you dating her?

864
00:56:16,036 --> 00:56:16,972
Really?

865
00:56:17,151 --> 00:56:18,335
I'm not!

866
00:56:18,936 --> 00:56:21,194
Why are you getting mad
when it's not true?

867
00:56:21,593 --> 00:56:23,077
This is about manners.

868
00:56:23,162 --> 00:56:24,512
Manners between friends.

869
00:56:24,597 --> 00:56:27,240
Good manners to someone who has
accepted me when I had nowhere to go

870
00:56:31,459 --> 00:56:33,802
Do you expect us to
understand right away?

871
00:56:34,479 --> 00:56:36,419
You should tell us in detail...

872
00:56:42,998 --> 00:56:44,212
We're sorry.

873
00:56:44,890 --> 00:56:46,486
We're just worried about you.

874
00:56:47,199 --> 00:56:48,131
I know.

875
00:56:48,385 --> 00:56:50,019
That's why I didn't say anything.

876
00:56:59,704 --> 00:57:01,940
Should I do it?

877
00:57:03,569 --> 00:57:04,480
Donate?

878
00:57:05,937 --> 00:57:06,787
Yes.

879
00:57:07,467 --> 00:57:09,716
You sure agree to it fast.

880
00:57:11,261 --> 00:57:12,098
And you.

881
00:57:12,183 --> 00:57:13,277
Are you still drunk?

882
00:57:13,362 --> 00:57:14,298
You're sober, right?

883
00:57:14,383 --> 00:57:15,889
She's completely sober.

884
00:57:15,974 --> 00:57:18,004
She didn't say she'll buy me a house.

885
00:57:18,994 --> 00:57:21,124
I only make promises I can keep.

886
00:57:22,769 --> 00:57:23,838
Are you going to the shoot now?

887
00:57:24,497 --> 00:57:25,592
I should.

888
00:57:25,916 --> 00:57:27,253
That's also a promise.

889
00:57:27,681 --> 00:57:28,878
I should keep it.

890
00:57:30,500 --> 00:57:32,309
Eunho, we're sorry.

891
00:57:32,982 --> 00:57:34,704
We were just worried.

892
00:57:35,999 --> 00:57:36,854
That's kind of you.

893
00:57:40,499 --> 00:57:41,902
I don't know about that.

894
00:57:45,897 --> 00:57:46,871
What is this?

895
00:57:46,956 --> 00:57:48,576
Did we get the time wrong?

896
00:57:49,729 --> 00:57:50,656
No, we didn't.

897
00:57:50,824 --> 00:57:52,008
What time does it suppose to start?

898
00:57:52,397 --> 00:57:53,575
We're even late.

899
00:57:53,660 --> 00:57:54,506
What?

900
00:57:58,788 --> 00:57:59,604
What is this?

901
00:57:59,689 --> 00:58:01,395
Be happy, Ms. Han Segye.

902
00:58:01,736 --> 00:58:03,174
From a fan of Han Segye.

903
00:58:07,946 --> 00:58:08,841
[Be happy, Ms. Han Segye]

904
00:58:17,132 --> 00:58:18,009
Thank you.

905
00:58:19,258 --> 00:58:20,572
Thanks for the food.

906
00:58:20,756 --> 00:58:22,021
-Thanks.
-Thank you.

907
00:58:29,611 --> 00:58:31,667
He's more peculiar than I thought he is.

908
00:58:31,779 --> 00:58:33,175
Your "Uncle", I mean.

909
00:58:35,064 --> 00:58:38,125
[Be happy, Ms. Han Segye.
From a fan of Han Segye]

910
00:59:17,576 --> 00:59:19,521
Do you only buy fish with all your money?

911
00:59:21,143 --> 00:59:23,123
What are you doing here?
You didn't even call me.

912
00:59:24,147 --> 00:59:27,270
Why should I call first
when I'm coming to my own company?

913
00:59:32,939 --> 00:59:37,355
What have you been doing?
Can't you do your job properly?

914
00:59:37,440 --> 00:59:39,038
I am doing it properly.

915
00:59:40,565 --> 00:59:41,426
I mean, my job.

916
00:59:41,830 --> 00:59:44,725
I heard you broke up with that model.

917
00:59:44,809 --> 00:59:46,774
I told you she's an actress, not a model.

918
00:59:47,493 --> 00:59:48,716
How did you know?

919
00:59:49,176 --> 00:59:52,373
Look it up on the internet.
That's all they've been talking about.

920
00:59:53,940 --> 00:59:58,042
How come you get dumped all the time?

921
00:59:58,389 --> 01:00:00,409
You fool...

922
01:00:01,589 --> 01:00:03,316
I'm so proud of you, Grandpa.

923
01:00:03,587 --> 01:00:04,684
You can even browse
the Internet on yourself.

924
01:00:04,769 --> 01:00:08,013
You can't even get one woman.
All you do is talk.

925
01:00:08,839 --> 01:00:10,426
That's enough. You should leave now.

926
01:00:10,809 --> 01:00:14,036
My heart is already in pieces
after being dumped.

927
01:00:14,248 --> 01:00:16,115
Do you want me to take care of it?

928
01:00:16,741 --> 01:00:18,509
You want to fix it with money?

929
01:00:18,669 --> 01:00:20,025
She's already rich herself.

930
01:00:20,110 --> 01:00:21,382
That's exactly...

931
01:00:21,647 --> 01:00:24,910
...why you got dumped.

932
01:00:26,445 --> 01:00:29,909
You should give her
what she needs the most.

933
01:00:30,477 --> 01:00:33,242
You're a businessman.
You don't even know that?

934
01:00:38,466 --> 01:00:40,628
What she wants the most...

935
01:00:42,155 --> 01:00:44,831
...is not to see me ever again.

936
01:00:45,245 --> 01:00:47,351
You fool.

937
01:01:06,629 --> 01:01:08,207
Yes, we're broken.

938
01:01:08,748 --> 01:01:10,364
Both you and I.

939
01:01:12,916 --> 01:01:15,313
But now I know you exist...

940
01:01:16,405 --> 01:01:18,418
...that's why I came out to the world.

941
01:01:20,375 --> 01:01:21,434
I thought maybe...

942
01:01:23,245 --> 01:01:25,323
...you've been waiting for me too.

943
01:01:32,062 --> 01:01:33,468
You're right. I have been waiting.

944
01:01:34,644 --> 01:01:37,619
So I could shove your broken life
into the dumpster.

945
01:01:58,502 --> 01:01:59,791
Cut. Okay.

946
01:02:00,249 --> 01:02:01,562
It's a cut. We're moving on!

947
01:02:01,647 --> 01:02:04,021
Please prepare for the next scene, C-5.

948
01:02:04,106 --> 01:02:05,812
Let's prepare for the next scene.

949
01:02:05,897 --> 01:02:07,147
Makeup, please.

950
01:02:12,059 --> 01:02:13,728
Hey, where is did it go?

951
01:02:19,557 --> 01:02:20,483
Hey.

952
01:02:20,729 --> 01:02:22,101
Will you really be okay?

953
01:02:22,185 --> 01:02:23,961
Should I ask the director
to stop shooting?

954
01:02:24,046 --> 01:02:26,523
I'm okay, there's only one scene left.

955
01:02:27,169 --> 01:02:28,627
I just need to do one more scene.

956
01:02:29,517 --> 01:02:30,903
I have a bad feeling though.

957
01:02:31,983 --> 01:02:34,012
I still have two days left.

958
01:02:34,211 --> 01:02:36,843
Five days before and after
have always been risky.

959
01:02:39,633 --> 01:02:40,701
It's okay.

960
01:02:41,014 --> 01:02:42,234
I think I'll be fine.

961
01:02:55,887 --> 01:02:58,612
You're my mistake and imperfection.

962
01:02:59,495 --> 01:03:00,857
Once you disappear,

963
01:03:02,448 --> 01:03:04,293
I'll be complete.

964
01:03:35,259 --> 01:03:36,383
Cut, okay.

965
01:03:36,468 --> 01:03:37,568
Okay!

966
01:04:10,249 --> 01:04:11,429
Are you okay?

967
01:04:27,409 --> 01:04:28,966
How old am I now?

968
01:04:33,699 --> 01:04:35,874
Sir, sir!

969
01:04:35,959 --> 01:04:38,709
One of the child actors
couldn't come because he fell ill.

970
01:04:38,794 --> 01:04:39,641
What?

971
01:04:40,569 --> 01:04:41,811
Darn it...

972
01:04:42,764 --> 01:04:45,025
-Director Lee will flip out.
-I know.

973
01:04:46,569 --> 01:04:47,488
What should I do?

974
01:04:48,889 --> 01:04:50,925
Hey, he has no lines anyway...

975
01:04:51,010 --> 01:04:52,619
...let's just get a random kid.

976
01:04:52,704 --> 01:04:54,563
-He just needs to stand there.
-Got it.

977
01:04:54,744 --> 01:04:55,981
Get on it quick!

978
01:04:59,479 --> 01:05:01,623
For some reason, I had a feeling
that I should...

979
01:05:02,719 --> 01:05:03,951
...bring children clothes.

980
01:05:08,675 --> 01:05:10,096
What size are these clothes?

981
01:05:10,844 --> 01:05:12,148
They're for nine to ten-year-olds.

982
01:05:16,956 --> 01:05:18,564
Let's just say I'm 10 years old.

983
01:05:19,039 --> 01:05:20,392
So that we're closer in age.

984
01:05:21,306 --> 01:05:22,469
But you look younger than that.

985
01:05:33,486 --> 01:05:34,655
Wait...

986
01:05:34,739 --> 01:05:37,855
He doesn't know how to act at all!

987
01:05:37,939 --> 01:05:39,077
Another kid will say the lines.

988
01:05:39,162 --> 01:05:41,115
He just needs to stand there. That's all!

989
01:05:41,199 --> 01:05:42,225
Thank you in advance!

990
01:05:42,310 --> 01:05:44,370
No! You can't!

991
01:05:54,439 --> 01:05:57,103
Why... don't we have a mom?

992
01:05:57,188 --> 01:05:58,066
Cut.

993
01:06:00,766 --> 01:06:01,966
Shall we try again?

994
01:06:06,091 --> 01:06:06,957
Action.

995
01:06:07,766 --> 01:06:09,895
Why... don't we have a mom?

996
01:06:09,979 --> 01:06:11,021
Cut, cut.

997
01:06:13,245 --> 01:06:14,674
Take it slow. Say it slowly.

998
01:06:14,968 --> 01:06:15,861
Try it again.

999
01:06:18,389 --> 01:06:19,235
Action.

1000
01:06:19,377 --> 01:06:21,526
-Why... don't we...
-Cut.

1001
01:06:24,189 --> 01:06:25,157
Let's take a break.

1002
01:06:28,990 --> 01:06:31,427
I didn't want to butt in,
but I think I have to.

1003
01:06:35,458 --> 01:06:36,300
Hey, little kid.

1004
01:06:36,385 --> 01:06:37,283
Little kid?

1005
01:06:37,609 --> 01:06:38,525
Me?

1006
01:06:38,694 --> 01:06:39,557
Yes, you.

1007
01:06:39,798 --> 01:06:40,861
But you are a kid too.

1008
01:06:40,946 --> 01:06:42,091
That's right.

1009
01:06:42,560 --> 01:06:43,593
I'm a kid too.

1010
01:06:45,143 --> 01:06:46,164
Hey, friend.

1011
01:06:47,222 --> 01:06:48,434
Repeat after me.

1012
01:06:52,889 --> 01:06:54,195
Why don't we...

1013
01:06:55,049 --> 01:06:56,881
...have a mom?

1014
01:06:57,218 --> 01:06:59,470
Why... don't we have a mom?

1015
01:06:59,555 --> 01:07:01,599
No, no. Cut, cut.

1016
01:07:02,829 --> 01:07:04,147
That's not how it's done.

1017
01:07:08,589 --> 01:07:09,831
Why don't we...

1018
01:07:11,239 --> 01:07:13,090
...have a mom?

1019
01:07:14,419 --> 01:07:15,626
Like that.

1020
01:07:15,833 --> 01:07:19,326
Why... don't we have a mom?

1021
01:07:21,219 --> 01:07:22,296
Let him say the lines.

1022
01:07:26,400 --> 01:07:27,639
Why don't we...

1023
01:07:28,429 --> 01:07:30,393
...have a mom?

1024
01:07:32,372 --> 01:07:34,558
Then, where did I come from?

1025
01:07:36,048 --> 01:07:38,412
Where do I go back to?

1026
01:07:50,439 --> 01:07:51,296
Cut.

1027
01:07:51,539 --> 01:07:52,322
Nice!

1028
01:07:52,407 --> 01:07:53,356
Good job.

1029
01:07:58,561 --> 01:07:59,580
What's your name?

1030
01:08:00,022 --> 01:08:01,058
Where's your mom?

1031
01:08:01,299 --> 01:08:03,436
You're a really good actor.

1032
01:08:03,593 --> 01:08:04,435
Do you have an agent?

1033
01:08:04,853 --> 01:08:07,354
I'm from DM...

1034
01:08:07,439 --> 01:08:08,675
Hey.

1035
01:08:09,033 --> 01:08:11,329
He's already taken.

1036
01:08:12,920 --> 01:08:15,820
My gosh. You did great, my actor.

1037
01:08:16,797 --> 01:08:18,334
He's signed to World Entertainment.

1038
01:08:23,229 --> 01:08:26,299
I think I should buy a child car seat.

1039
01:08:26,384 --> 01:08:27,350
I'm sorry.

1040
01:08:27,435 --> 01:08:28,933
Don't be sorry.

1041
01:08:29,018 --> 01:08:31,584
You even shoot an extra scene.

1042
01:08:31,819 --> 01:08:34,058
You really did a great job today.

1043
01:08:34,143 --> 01:08:35,453
Thanks for your hard work.

1044
01:08:36,221 --> 01:08:38,295
The production crew will be shooting
outside the city for a while.

1045
01:08:38,379 --> 01:08:40,044
So, don't worry about anything
and get some rest.

1046
01:08:40,129 --> 01:08:42,013
I was disappointed because
I didn't get the leading role.

1047
01:08:42,098 --> 01:08:43,125
But this is pretty nice.

1048
01:08:43,209 --> 01:08:46,365
Exactly. How about you keep taking
supporting roles from now on?

1049
01:08:46,449 --> 01:08:48,002
Isn't that a great idea?

1050
01:08:50,881 --> 01:08:51,987
By the way...

1051
01:08:53,048 --> 01:08:56,368
How do I go back home like this?

1052
01:09:32,806 --> 01:09:33,696
Get up.

1053
01:09:34,489 --> 01:09:35,369
Yay!

1054
01:09:35,454 --> 01:09:36,482
-Geez -Come on.

1055
01:09:36,749 --> 01:09:38,109
That's it!

1056
01:09:38,888 --> 01:09:39,947
We did it. Sit.

1057
01:09:41,589 --> 01:09:42,972
Ta-da!

1058
01:09:44,247 --> 01:09:45,096
Hey.

1059
01:09:45,371 --> 01:09:46,912
Do you really have to eat this?

1060
01:09:47,428 --> 01:09:49,145
Do you want me to rinse it for you?

1061
01:09:49,229 --> 01:09:51,165
I think it'll be too spicy for you.

1062
01:09:51,249 --> 01:09:52,958
-It's okay.
-No!

1063
01:09:53,179 --> 01:09:54,347
I don't think you will be.

1064
01:09:54,716 --> 01:09:55,715
Give me.

1065
01:09:56,339 --> 01:09:59,319
I know you're an adult in your heart,

1066
01:09:59,604 --> 01:10:01,173
but your stomach
still behaves like a child.

1067
01:10:01,258 --> 01:10:02,828
You shouldn't eat stuff like this.

1068
01:10:06,154 --> 01:10:08,062
I was craving spicy tteokbokki all day.

1069
01:10:08,147 --> 01:10:10,093
Me too.

1070
01:10:12,249 --> 01:10:14,069
Yes, it's so nice and spicy.

1071
01:10:18,281 --> 01:10:21,349
By the way, honestly,
I was scared earlier.

1072
01:10:21,434 --> 01:10:23,083
I really thought you would get caught.

1073
01:10:23,238 --> 01:10:24,774
-Me too.
-It's fine, it's over.

1074
01:10:24,859 --> 01:10:26,701
It's a relief that you didn't.

1075
01:10:26,786 --> 01:10:27,956
Eat up.

1076
01:10:28,484 --> 01:10:31,829
Enjoy, Segye.

1077
01:10:32,930 --> 01:10:34,511
